            <note xml:id="foot.f2">Wedgwood’s abstract has not been found. See also the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7562.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from Hensleigh Wedgwood, [after 9 March 1871]</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">Wedgwood refers to <hi rend="italic">Descent.</hi></note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">CD had discussed temperance as a self-regarding virtue in his <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7560.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to Hensleigh Wedgwood, 9 March 1871</ref>. See also <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1966.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi></ref> 1: 96–7.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f5">Wedgwood refers to the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7645.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from John Morley, 30 March 1871</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f6">Wedgwood probably refers to Associationism.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f7">Jane has not been identified.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f8">Wedgwood probably refers to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_7859.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Katherine Euphemia Wedgwood</ref>.</note>
        </div>        
            
